---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout pageKey="rooftop-solar-pratapgarh.html" headerVariant="guide">

<section class="py-20">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
<div class="inline-block bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold">Local Solar Guide · Pratapgarh, Uttar Pradesh</div>
<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold mt-6">Rooftop Solar in Pratapgarh</h1>
<p class="text-slate-600 text-lg mt-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">Pratapgarh homeowners are reducing PUVVNL electricity bills with rooftop solar and PM Surya Ghar subsidies. This guide covers costs, net metering, empanelled installers, and how to get started.</p>
<a href="index.html" class="inline-block mt-8 bg-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-2xl font-bold transition">Check My Solar Savings</a>
</div>
</section>

<section class="pb-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-5">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">DISCOM</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">PUVVNL</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">Purvanchal / UPPCL</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Avg Sun Hours</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">5–5.5 hrs/day</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">Annual average</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Central Subsidy</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2 text-emerald-700">Up to ₹78,000</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">For 3kW · verify at portal</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Typical Payback</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2 text-indigo-700">4–6 Years</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">After subsidy</div></div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Why Rooftop Solar Makes Sense in Pratapgarh</h2>
<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Good Solar Irradiance</h3><p class="text-slate-600">Pratapgarh receives approximately 5 to 5.5 peak sun hours daily — well suited for rooftop solar. Its location in the Gangetic plain ensures consistent sunlight with minimal natural shading for most homes.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Summer Bills & Solar Align</h3><p class="text-slate-600">Hot Pratapgarh summers drive the highest PUVVNL bills of the year. Solar panels generate most strongly through these same months, creating the best possible financial return on your solar investment.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Rising PUVVNL Tariffs</h3><p class="text-slate-600">PUVVNL domestic tariffs have increased over successive regulatory revisions. Rooftop solar locks in generation at zero marginal cost, insulating your household from future tariff hikes.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">PM Surya Ghar Eligibility</h3><p class="text-slate-600">Pratapgarh homeowners with a PUVVNL electricity connection are eligible for the PM Surya Ghar Muft Bijli Yojana central subsidy through pmsuryaghar.gov.in using a PUVVNL-empanelled installer.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">PUVVNL Net Metering in Pratapgarh</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">How the net metering connection process works for Pratapgarh homeowners under PUVVNL.</p>
<div class="space-y-4">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Install via PUVVNL-Empanelled Installer</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Verify your installer is empanelled with PUVVNL on pmsuryaghar.gov.in before signing any contract. Only empanelled installations qualify for the central subsidy.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Submit Net Metering Application to PUVVNL</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">After installation, your installer submits the net metering application to PUVVNL. Most empanelled installers handle this paperwork on your behalf.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">PUVVNL Technical Inspection</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">A PUVVNL engineer inspects the installation to verify grid safety compliance. This typically takes two to four weeks.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">4</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Bi-Directional Meter Installation</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Your PUVVNL meter is replaced with a net meter measuring both electricity imported and exported. A one-time meter replacement fee may apply.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">5</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Commissioning & Net Metering Active</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Once commissioned, surplus solar exported earns credits on your monthly PUVVNL electricity bill going forward.</p></div></div>
</div>
<p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-6">See our <a href="learn/net-metering-india.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">net metering guide</a> for a full explanation of how bill credits work.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">System Sizes for Pratapgarh Homeowners</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Match your monthly PUVVNL bill to the right system size.</p>
<div class="overflow-x-auto">
<table class="w-full text-sm bg-white rounded-2xl border overflow-hidden">
<thead class="bg-slate-50"><tr><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Monthly PUVVNL Bill</th><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Recommended Size</th><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Roof Area</th><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Best For</th></tr></thead>
<tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
<tr><td class="p-4">₹600 – ₹1,500</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="1kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">1kW System</a></td><td class="p-4">80–120 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Small homes</td></tr>
<tr><td class="p-4">₹1,200 – ₹2,500</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="2kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">2kW System</a></td><td class="p-4">160–220 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Small families</td></tr>
<tr class="bg-emerald-50"><td class="p-4">₹2,000 – ₹4,000</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="3kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">3kW System</a> ★ Most popular</td><td class="p-4">240–300 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Medium families</td></tr>
<tr><td class="p-4">₹4,000+</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="5kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">5kW System</a></td><td class="p-4">400–500 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Larger homes</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-4">Use our <a href="learn/solar-system-sizing-guide.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">solar system sizing guide</a> for the full methodology.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-emerald-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">PM Surya Ghar Subsidy in Pratapgarh</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Pratapgarh homeowners with a PUVVNL connection can apply for the PM Surya Ghar central subsidy through pmsuryaghar.gov.in.</p>
<div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">Up to 2kW</div><div class="text-2xl font-bold text-emerald-700">₹30,000/kW</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">Central subsidy · verify at portal</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">3kW System Total</div><div class="text-2xl font-bold text-emerald-700">Up to ₹78,000</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">3rd kW at lower per-kW rate</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">Above 3kW</div><div class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-700">No central subsidy</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">Beyond 3kW capacity</div></div>
</div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-bold mb-3">How to Apply as a Pratapgarh Homeowner</h3>
<ol class="space-y-2 text-slate-700 text-sm">
<li>1. Register at <strong>pmsuryaghar.gov.in</strong> using your PUVVNL consumer number</li>
<li>2. Select a PUVVNL-empanelled installer from the portal</li>
<li>3. Get system installed, net metering connected, PUVVNL commissioning done</li>
<li>4. Complete subsidy disbursement application on the portal</li>
<li>5. Subsidy credited directly to your bank account</li>
</ol>
<p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-4">Verify current subsidy amounts at pmsuryaghar.gov.in before applying.</p>
</div>
<div class="mt-4"><a href="learn/pm-surya-ghar-guide.html" class="inline-flex items-center text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline text-sm">Read the full PM Surya Ghar guide →</a></div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Pratapgarh Areas We Serve</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">We help homeowners across Pratapgarh district connect with PUVVNL-empanelled installers.</p>
<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
{["Pratapgarh City", "Belha", "Kunda", "Sandwa", "Patti", "Mandhata", "Rampur Khas", "Antu", "Raniganj", "Shivganj", "Gaura", "Lalganj", "Koraon"].map(area => (
  <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-slate-100 rounded-full text-sm text-slate-700 font-medium">{area}</span>
))}
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions — Pratapgarh Solar</h2>
<div class="space-y-4">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">Which electricity company handles rooftop solar in Pratapgarh?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Pratapgarh falls under <strong>PUVVNL (Purvanchal Vidyut Vitran Nigam Limited)</strong>, a UPPCL subsidiary covering eastern UP. All net metering and solar scheme empanelment are processed through PUVVNL.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">How do I apply for net metering in Pratapgarh?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">After installation by a PUVVNL-empanelled installer, your installer submits the net metering application to PUVVNL. PUVVNL inspects the system and installs a bi-directional meter. Typically takes two to six weeks.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">Is PM Surya Ghar subsidy available in Pratapgarh?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Yes. Pratapgarh homeowners with a PUVVNL connection are eligible. Use a PUVVNL-empanelled installer and apply at pmsuryaghar.gov.in. Verify current amounts before applying.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">What solar system size suits most Pratapgarh homes?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">For most Pratapgarh homes with monthly bills of ₹1,000–₹3,500, a 1kW to 3kW system is appropriate. Homes with AC use through summer benefit most from 2kW or 3kW systems.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">How much does rooftop solar cost in Pratapgarh?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Pre-subsidy cost ranges from ₹60,000 to ₹80,000 per kW. After PM Surya Ghar subsidy (up to ₹78,000 for 3kW), net cost is significantly lower. Get quotes from at least two PUVVNL-empanelled installers.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">Is Pratapgarh a good location for solar?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Yes. Pratapgarh receives approximately 5 to 5.5 peak sun hours daily. Hot summers mean high solar generation coincides with peak demand, making solar financially effective for most homeowners.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-10">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<div class="bg-indigo-50 border border-indigo-100 rounded-2xl p-6">
<p class="text-slate-700 text-sm">Also serving homeowners in <a href="rooftop-solar-prayagraj.html" class="text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline">Prayagraj</a> and <a href="rooftop-solar-varanasi.html" class="text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline">Varanasi</a> — both under PUVVNL with the same net metering process. <a href="cities.html" class="text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline">View all city guides →</a></p>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Helpful Guides for Pratapgarh Homeowners</h2>
<div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
<a href="learn/pm-surya-ghar-guide.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Subsidies</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">PM Surya Ghar Guide</div></a>
<a href="learn/net-metering-india.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Billing</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">Net Metering Guide</div></a>
<a href="learn/how-to-choose-solar-installer.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Installers</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">How to Choose an Installer</div></a>
<a href="learn/solar-system-sizing-guide.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Sizing</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">Solar System Sizing Guide</div></a>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-20">
<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
<div class="bg-slate-900 text-white rounded-[2rem] p-10">
<h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">See How Much You Can Save in Pratapgarh</h2>
<p class="text-slate-300 mb-8">Get a personalised solar savings estimate based on your PUVVNL bill — in under 60 seconds.</p>
<a href="index.html" class="inline-block bg-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-700 px-8 py-4 rounded-2xl font-bold transition">Calculate My Solar Savings</a>
</div>
</div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
